description:
For a research project, I am extracting statistics about the content on RDF bases. To avoid using several nested blank nodes and to be able to gather the stats concerning the same classes and properties from my dozen of queries, I sent to DBpedia the following query where I generate Uris.
PREFIX prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#>
PREFIX earl: <http://www.w3.org/ns/earl#>
PREFIX kgi: <http://ns.inria.fr/kg/index#>
PREFIX void: <http://rdfs.org/ns/void#>
CONSTRUCT {
    kgi:dbpediaMetadata a prov:Entity , earl:TestSubject ;
        prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://dbpedia.org/sparql> ;
        kgi:curated kgi:dbpediaDataset .
    kgi:dbpediaDataset void:classPartition ?classPartition .
    GRAPH ?sportalGraph {
        ?classPartition void:class ?c ;
            void:propertyPartition ?classPropPartition .
            ?classPropPartition void:property ?p ;
                void:triples ?x .
     }
}
WHERE {
    { SELECT ?c (COUNT(?o) AS ?x) ?p WHERE { ?s a ?c ; ?p ?o } GROUP BY ?c ?p }
    BIND( IRI( CONCAT( str(kgi:), str(?c) ) ) AS ?classPartition )
    BIND( IRI( CONCAT( str(?classPartition), str(?p) ) ) AS ?classPropPartition )
    BIND( IRI( CONCAT( str(kgi:dbpediaDataset), "Statistics" ) ) AS ?sportalGraph )
 }

I obtained the following error, that I do not understand:
Virtuoso 42000 Error GBJON: Partitioned hash table must be of the chash type
Sending the version of the query without the concatenation, with nested blank nodes, does not create the error.
